cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.LG

This paper deals with the problem of utilizing correlated event reports across languages for early warning systems that detect natural disasters. It involves text mining, temporal aberration detection algorithms, and automated health surveillance. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for tracking the evolution of disease outbreaks. Hence, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the second likely category. The paper also deals with complex spatiotemporal events, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves comparative analysis and evaluation of models, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper involves machine learning techniques for automated health surveillance, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
